        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles east of Powder River Pass, which is 16 miles south of Buffalo,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Johnson
County.

This includes Interstate 25 between mile markers 281 and 288.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
